# ðŸ“° News API Backend

This project is a REST API built with Node.js + Express + TypeScript that consumes data from NewsAPI.org
It allows you to list news sources, get top headlines, and search for articles.

## ðŸ› ï¸ Technologies & Libraries

- Backend framework: Express
- Language: TypeScript
- HTTP client: Axios
- Environment variables: dotenv
- Nodemon (dev dependency) for auto-reloading
- ts-node-dev (dev dependency) for TypeScript runtime in development


## ðŸ“Œ Requirements

Before running the project locally, make sure you have installed:
- Node.js >= 18
- npm >= 9
- A valid API key from NewsAPI https://newsapi.org/

### 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/SamQuintero/tareas_backend.git
cd tareas_backend/tarea1

### 2. Install dependencies
npm install

### 3. Configure environment variables

.env file example:
API_KEY=your_api_key_here
 
### 4. Run the project
Development mode
npm run dev

Build and run in production
npm run build
npm start

API will be available at:
ðŸ‘‰ http://localhost:3000

## ðŸ“¡ Available Endpoints
ðŸ”¹ Sources
GET /api/sources

ðŸ”¹ Top Headlines
GET /api/headlines?country=us&category=technology
Parameters: country, category, sources, q

ðŸ”¹ Everything (search articles)
GET /api/everything?q=bitcoin
Parameters: q (required), from, to, language, sortBy